5|$|Speaking at a Chautauqua {{conference in}} Jūrmala, Latvia in June 1986, Matlock <b>told</b> <b>the</b> <b>crowd</b> that the United States did not {{recognize}} the incorporation of the Baltic States into the Soviet Union. His remarks are credited by Dainis Īvāns, leader of the Popular Front of Latvia, with galvanizing the independence movement in Latvia.|$|E
