25|$|Richie <b>told</b> <b>the</b> <b>crowd</b> {{that his}} {{grandmother}} {{was diagnosed with}} breast cancer in her 80s, but survived and lived until she was 103 years old. He stated that she was his enduring symbol of hope and his reason for becoming a breast cancer activist.|$|E
5000|$|During {{a memorable}} game in 2003, Shreve <b>told</b> <b>the</b> arena <b>crowd</b> in Cleveland {{to stay calm}} after Ron Artest (then of the Indiana Pacers) made obscene {{gestures}} to the audience. When Shreve advised <b>the</b> <b>crowd</b> not to throw anything onto the court, Artest, who {{was sitting on the}} scorers table, patted Shreve on the back. http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/basketball/news/2003/04/02/pacers_cavs_ap ...|$|R
